This directory contains some examples of using TBX.

Each application has a !Help file giving details of what they demonstrate.

Inside each directory is included a src sub-directory containing
the source code for the example and a makefile to build the example.

All examples are released under the same copyright as TBX (The X11 License).
See the COPYING file in the TBX directory for details.

The examples are:

!TbxMin   - This is a minimum tbx application
!Reverser - Show how to use objects and events
!StopWatch - use of a timer
!IconView - A simple application showing how to create a "filer-like" view
!TbxDocEx - Shows a document type application
!Graphics - Shows use of OffsetGraphics class to draw shapes, text and images
